# Strategy Layer Rules

Use the `algo-strategy` skill when editing these files.

## Required pattern

```python
class MyStrategy(BaseStrategy):
    name = "my_strategy"

    def __init__(self, params: dict):
        super().__init__(params)
        self.subscription = DataSubscription(
            symbols=params.get("symbols", []),
            intervals=[params.get("interval", "1d")],
            tick=params.get("tick", False),
        )
```

## Checklist for new strategy

- [ ] Extends `BaseStrategy`
- [ ] Declares `DataSubscription` matching `on_bar` / `on_tick`
- [ ] Parameters from YAML via `self.params`
- [ ] Registered in `src/strategy/registry.py`
- [ ] Unit test in `tests/test_<name>.py`
- [ ] No `import futu` in strategy files

## Runner mapping

- Daily K → `run_paper.py --mode daily`
- 1m → `run_paper.py --mode intraday --data 1m`
- Tick → `run_tick.py` (separate process)
